# Conventional Commit Template
#
# CI enforces Conventional Commits on pull requests.
# Use this template to avoid lint failures.
# When drafting PRs, trim unused changelog sections.
#
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Allowed types:
# feat:      New feature (triggers MINOR release)
# fix:       Bug fix (triggers PATCH release)
# docs:      Documentation changes
# style:     Formatting, whitespace, no code changes
# refactor:  Code restructure (not fix/feature)
# perf:      Performance improvements
# test:      Tests only
# build:     Build system or dependencies
# ci:        CI configuration or scripts
# chore:     Misc changes (no src or tests)
# revert:    Revert a previous commit
#
# Example: feat(panel): support translated sections
#
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

# -- Guidelines -------------------------------------------------------
# Testing:
# - Note commands you ran (composer test, pnpm test). If you skipped suites, explain why.
# Documentation:
# - Mention doc updates or state “docs: n/a” so reviewers know whether guidance changed.
# -- Formatting -------------------------------------------------------
# Subject:
# - Max 50 characters
# - Imperative mood (e.g. "add", "update", "fix")
# - No trailing period
#
# Leave one blank line before the body.
#
# Body (optional):
# - Explain WHAT and WHY (not HOW)
# - Wrap lines at 72 characters
# - Use plain prose; Conventional Commit formatting is only required for
#   the subject line
# - Emojis allowed here (e.g. ✨) if helpful
#
# Footer (optional):
# - Closes #12
# - BREAKING CHANGE: description
# - Co-authored-by: Name <email>
#
# -- Helpful Gitmoji Reference -----------------------------
# These are NOT required, but may be used in the body for common types:
#
# ✨ feat (new features)
# 🐛 fix (bug fixes)
# 📝 docs (documentation)
# 🎨 style (formatting/style)
# ♻️ refactor (code restructure)
# ⚡️ perf (performance)
# 🧪 test (tests)
# 🏗️ build (build system/deps)
# 🚀 ci (CI/CD)
# 🔧 chore (misc)
# 🔒 security (security fixes)
# ⬆️ upgrade (dependency upgrades)
# ⬇️ downgrade (dependency downgrades)
# 🚨 lint (fix linter warnings)
# 🚧 wip (work in progress)
#
# For more options, see https://gitmoji.dev
